title: Unemployment rate in Turkey 2019
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 5 significant trends.
The longest trend is moderately positive which exists from 2006 to 1999.
In a similar manner, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2016 to 2012.
Correspondingly, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2019 to 2016.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2012 to 2009.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2009 to 2006.
gold: The statistic shows the unemployment rate in Turkey from 1999 to 2019 . In 2019 , the unemployment rate in Turkey was at about 11.9 percent . Trade in Turkey Turkey is a growing market and recognized as one of the world 's newest industrialized countries .
